{{Infobox theatre | name = Red Eye Theater | image = | image_size = | caption = | address = 15 West 14th St. | city = [[Minneapolis, Minnesota|Minneapolis]], [[Minnesota|MN]] 55403 | country = [[United States]] | capacity = 100 | opened = 1983 | website = {{URL|redeyetheater.org}} }}
'''Red Eye Theater''' (legal name '''Red Eye Collaboration''') is a multidisciplinary creative laboratory dedicated to the development and presentation of new theater and performance work in [[Minneapolis, Minnesota]]. It was founded in 1983 by writer/director Steve Busa, performer Miriam Must and visual artist Barbara Abramson.<ref> Collins, Robert; "Expect the Unexpected"; Mpls.St.Paul Magazine; November, 1985. </ref>
Branching out from a theatrical base to support a wide range of programming, Red Eye is home to theater, dance, music, performance art, and interdisciplinary forms. Each year Red Eye presents two company productions, the ''New Works 4 Weeks'' festival, and co-sponsored projects by local companies and independent artists.
''New Works 4 Weeks'' is a multidisciplinary festival that is the culminating public component of a six-month development program geared toward emerging artists engaged in the investigation of new directions.
Red Eye has received major funding from the Jerome Foundation,<ref>[http://www.jeromefdn.org/grantees?keyword=Red+Eye+Collaboration&op=Search&form_build_id=form-uBzHsiQSQo6bjAUMh5l4Aclc5uOQb6ESAbmuZRO_j9c&form_id=jerome_search_form Grantees], Jerome Foundation Website. Retrieved August 6, 2015.</ref> the [[McKnight Foundation]],<ref>[https://www.mcknight.org/grant-programs/grantees?query=Red+Eye+Collaboration&year=&program_area=Arts Grantee Database], McKnight Foundation website. Retrieved August 6, 2015.</ref> [[Target Corporation]], the Metropolitan Regional Arts Council,<ref>[http://www.mrac.org/news/recent-grant-awards#Capital%20Grant%20Awards Recent Grant Awards], Metropolitan Regional Arts Council website. Retrieved August 6, 2015.</ref> the Minnesota State Arts Board,<ref>[http://www.arts.state.mn.us/grants/2016/2016-awarded-opsup.htm FY 2016 Grants Awarded] Minnesota State Arts Board website. Retrieved August 6, 2015.</ref> the Clean Water Land & Legacy Amendment,<ref>[http://www.legacy.leg.mn/projects/project/9?keys=Red%20Eye%20Collaboration Search Results], Minnesota's Legacy Website. Retrieved August 10, 2015.</ref> and the [[National Endowment for the Arts]].<ref>[http://arts.gov/sites/default/files/Fall_2014_Art_Works_Grants_by_Discipline_FINAL.pdf National Endowment for the Arts — December 2014 Grant Announcement: Art Works grants] Retrieved August 6, 2015.</ref>
