'''Zrće''' ({{IPA-sh|zr̩̂ːt͡ɕɛ|pron}}) is a long pebble beach on the [[Adriatic Sea|Adriatic]] island of [[Pag (island)|Pag]] in the northern part of the [[Croatia]]n coast. It is located near [[Novalja]] and [[Gajac]], about {{convert|2|km|0|abbr=off}} from the town's center. It is one of over 100 [[Blue Flag beach]]es in Croatia, having been given the award in 2003.
The beach is a Croatian summer destination for partygoers, with several all-hours [[discotheque]]s and beach bars operating during summer months. It regularly features [[gig (musical performance)|gig]]s by internationally known [[house music|house]] and [[trance music|trance]] [[disc jockey|DJs]] at the peak of the Croatian summer season in July and August. "Papaya" is a [[Nightclub|club]] on Zrće beach which has hosted DJs and festivals including [[Godskitchen]] and [[Swedish House Mafia]]. In 2010, ''[[DJ Magazine]]'' voted Papaya Club #32 in its Top 100 venues in the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.djmag.com/top100clubs/?op=detail&start&page=4&year=2011&id=332 |title=Top 100 Clubs |publisher=Djmag.com |date= |accessdate=2012-03-19}}</ref> and [[Axwell]] named the club his gig of the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.djmag.com/top100/detail/2594 |title=DJ Mag |publisher=DJ Mag |date= |accessdate=2012-03-19}}</ref> Papaya has hosted Hideout festival in conjunction with Aquarius, also on Zrce beach since 2011. In 2011, Papaya Club hosted a heat of Miss Clubs, an international beauty contest.
